This week's mark is one we did a long time ago for Seeds Ministries - started by one of our favorite clients and a nonprofit that seeks to help fund and facilitate faith based ministries. In essence setting them free from financial concerns to do the ministry they were called to do. Hence the butterfly emerging from the wheat stalk. The name and logo have led to a lot of interesting conversations as we have travelled the world with them. And isn't what you would hope a brand could do? #logo #logos #graphicdesign #seed #ministry #missions

Before you GOSSIP about them, CHOOSE to PRAY for them. We ALL have been apart of this at some point BUT honestly, Instead of gossiping about them and the situation, which doesn't help them or change the situation. I choose to pray for them and about the situation because prayer changes everything not idle chatter

“A man of knowledge uses words with restraint, and a man of understanding is even-tempered.” -Proverbs 17:27 Guest writer, Nichole Kauffman  on Proverbs 17 - "Restraining words was not something I was used to. -------------------------------
After all, in a world where everyone talks so loud, you have to shout to be heard. And so I shouted.

Sometimes it was just a story about my day, other times it was an opinion. And many others, it was an argument founded on the desire to be heard and the desire to be right.
-------------------------------
But as I processed this newfound truth, Jesus began to teach me something"... more on how Nichole found freedom in communication by seeking God for wisdom with her words, especially in marriage on the blog {RefocusedBibleStudy.com} link in profile
